column96: Trust wasn't established from the beginning. I wanted to incorporate electronics to make a 3 axis phone gimbal and they said go for it but were not going to help you, you're completely on your own. So being the man I am, I took that as a challenge and designed all the parts, did all the research, put everything together, and went through dozens of hours of trouble shooting. And at the very end of the project, what they do is say "hey you're not done in time so were going with the shittier design that doesn't work instead". Do you know how heartbreaking that is? So instead of taking that as an answer I spent like 60 hours that week redesign, rewiring, buying parts, breaking parts, until it finally worked and so I got it to work but at the cost of my Sanity the left week of school before dead week. I think having people voice their opinions rather than a 1 versus 2 the entire semester would have been way better because the other 3 people were either absent physically or disconnected from conversation physically so it was just so insanely frustrating to work with those people especially when you know it need to be done the right way but instead they chose otherwise while expecting me to do all the fricken work. I spent at least 100 hours whereas they didn't do shit other than complain and speak for everyone. Sorry.

column96: Trust wasn't established from the beginning. I wanted to incorporate electronics to make a 3 axis phone gimbal and they said go for it but were not going to help you, you're completely on your own. So being the man I am, I took that as a challenge and designed all the parts, did all the research, put everything together, and went through dozens of hours of trouble shooting. And at the very end of the project, what they do is say "hey you're not done in time so were going with the shittier design that doesn't work instead". Do you know how heartbreaking that is? So instead of taking that as an answer I spent like 60 hours that week redesign, rewiring, buying parts, breaking parts, until it finally worked and so I got it to work but at the cost of my Sanity the left week of school before dead week. I think having people voice their opinions rather than a 1 versus 2 the entire semester would have been way better because the other 3 people were either absent physically or disconnected from conversation physically so it was just so insanely frustrating to work with those people especially when you know it need to be done the right way but instead they chose otherwise while expecting me to do all the fricken work. I spent at least 100 hours whereas they didn't do shit other than complain and speak for everyone. Sorry.

column100: For my own contributions I will be qualitative. During Spring break I spent 6+ hours trouble shooting the printer with Jay at my house. During Cal day Jay and I again worked on the printer for 5 hours at my house. I edited and submitted a video for our printer progress report. I spent 2 hours studying how to the water jet works and setting up the cut path for our job on OMAX Layout so that Andrew could just upload that file and run the machine. I created 3 of the 5 GD&T Drawings. I've been handling meeting logistics and helped film for our video. I went to Ace to pick up last minute bolts for the project.
